sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  actor App as Solid client app
  participant IDP as Solid-OIDC IdP<br/>(openidconnect)
  participant Reg as /register<br/>(RFC 7591)
  participant Pod as solid-pod-rs<br/>Resource server

  rect rgba(139,92,246,0.15)
    Note over App,IDP: 1. Dynamic Client Registration (RFC 7591)
    App->>Reg: POST /register { redirect_uris, token_endpoint_auth_method }
    Reg-->>App: ClientRegistrationResponse { client_id }
  end

  rect rgba(0,212,255,0.15)
    Note over App,IDP: 2. Discovery + authorisation
    App->>IDP: GET /.well-known/openid-configuration
    IDP-->>App: DiscoveryDocument { authorization_endpoint, token_endpoint, jwks_uri, dpop_signing_alg_values_supported }
    App->>IDP: /authorize (code flow + PKCE)
    IDP-->>App: authorization code
  end

  rect rgba(245,158,11,0.15)
    Note over App,IDP: 3. DPoP-bound token request
    App->>App: Generate JWK keypair → compute jkt = thumbprint(pk)
    App->>App: Build DPoP proof JWT { htm:"POST", htu:"/token", jti, iat, jwk:pk }
    App->>IDP: POST /token (code, DPoP: <proof>)
    IDP->>IDP: Bind access_token.cnf.jkt = jkt
    IDP-->>App: access_token (JWT, cnf.jkt=<thumbprint>)
  end

  rect rgba(16,185,129,0.15)
    Note over App,Pod: 4. Resource request + DPoP verification
    App->>App: Build NEW DPoP proof { htm:"PUT", htu:"<pod>/alice/notes/foo.ttl", ath:hash(access_token) }
    App->>Pod: PUT /alice/notes/foo.ttl<br/>Authorization: DPoP <access_token><br/>DPoP: <proof>
    Pod->>Pod: verify_dpop_proof(proof, method, url)
    Pod->>Pod: verify_access_token(token) → claims.cnf.jkt
    alt jkt mismatch
      Pod-->>App: 401 invalid_dpop_proof
    else ok
      Pod->>Pod: extract_webid(claims) → WebID IRI
      Pod->>Pod: WAC check against WebID
      Pod-->>App: 201 Created
    end
  end
